The paper proposes a method for fine-grained image categorization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The method is based on machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of multi-scale part proposals, which is related to object detection and segmentation (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on three challenging datasets, which involves information retrieval and classification (cs.IR).
